<page columns=1 padding=16 name=About background=Edoc_bg.png edge_scaling linkcolor=#f0f0f0>
  <font face=vixar/20 color=#d3e5ff>
  <p align=100%>
  About
  <p>
    <font face=vixar/14 color=#d3e5ff>
    So, here it is kids...
    <p>
    <p>
    ...My interperetation of Shamrock/Transition for enlightenment.
    I didn't change too much, just the basic colour scheme (and maybe a few
    parts of the border layout). In effect all the hard work has been done by
    other people, I just glued the bits together.
    <p>
    <p>
    This theme was inspired by the screenshot of transition by dangeruss
    http://dangeruss.deviantart.com and the shamrock theme by hippy
    http://hippy.deviantart.com Both afore mentioned designers have given me 
    permission to create this.
    <p>
    <p>
    I just got a bit carried away with a few of the elements so I'm guessing
    this is more of a hack than a port.
    <p>
    <p align=100%>
    Still aiming for clean tho...

<page columns=1 padding=16 name=Useage background=Edoc_bg.png edge_scaling linkcolor=#f0f0f0>
  <font face=vixar/20 color=#d3e5ff>
  <p align=100%>
  Concept & Useage
  <p>
    <font face=vixar/14 color=#d3e5ff>

    The origional theme (to the best of my knowledge) had mouse over ONLY widgets. I
    decided to change this and replace the top right close with a raise/lower button 
    (right click = raise/ left click = lower)
    <p>
    I also added the close button to the left hand side (to avoid accidental closeage
    ;) It sits pretty much out of the way until needed.
    <p>
    Most of the dialogs were a total re-fit and the colour scheme was inspired by the
    R-9 fighter (yes, the one from R-Type) hence the name.
    <p>
    <p>
    <p>
    <p>
    <p>
    <p align=100%>
    I hope you all enjoy useing this theme
    <p align=100%>
    bugs, hassles etc... mailto:babyhead@lostmypants.net

